-- Pamodzi Hotels of Zambia Says it Posts a First-Half Profit of $34 Million
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-12-23T09:15:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/pamodzi-hotels-of-zambia-says-it-posts-a-first-half-profit-of-34-million.html
Pamodzi Hotels Plc of Zambia said it
posted first-half profit in the six months to Sept. 30 of 1.61
billion kwacha, or 16 kwacha per share.  Revenue for the period was 23.48 billion kwacha, the
Lusaka-based company said in a statement posted late yesterday
on the African is Cool investor relations website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  